---
// No props needed
---

<section
  class="pt-8 md:pt-20 pb-8"
  style="background-color: hsl(220 14% 96%); width: 100vw; position: relative; left: 50%; right: 50%; margin-left: -50vw; margin-right: -50vw;"
>
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">

      
      <!-- ─── H2-1: How the Xbox Gamertag Generator Works ─── -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2
          class="mt-6 mb-4"
          style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 1.75rem); font-weight: 700; color: hsl(107 76% 26%); line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
        >
          How the Xbox Gamertag Generator Works
        </h2>

        <p class="mb-4" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
          The Xbox Gamertag Generator creates name ideas based on the options you choose. You can filter by gender style, character theme, language, and name preference to get results that feel more personal and Xbox-ready — whether you want something funny, cool, aesthetic, sweaty, cute, or clean.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-3" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
          Here is how to use it:
        </p>

        <ol class="mb-6 space-y-2" style="list-style: decimal; padding-left: 1.5rem;">
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            Choose a gender style — <strong style="color: #111827;">male, female, or neutral</strong>
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            Select a character theme — <strong style="color: #111827;">animals, fantasy, gaming, music, space, food, funny, sports, or tech</strong>
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            Choose your preferred language — <strong style="color: #111827;">English, Japanese, Spanish, Arabic, and 11 more</strong>
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            Set your name preference — <strong style="color: #111827;">default, short name, no numbers, or short with no numbers</strong>
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            Add an optional word in the Include field to personalize your results
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            Click Generate to get your Xbox gamertag ideas
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            Pick your favorite name from the results
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            Check if your name is available using our
            <a href="/xbox-gamertag-availability-checker" style="color: hsl(107 76% 26%); text-decoration: underline; font-weight: 600;">Xbox Gamertag Availability Checker</a>
            before using it — if the base name is already taken, Xbox may add a number suffix automatically
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <!-- ─── H2-2: Generator Options Explained ─── -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2
          class="mt-6 mb-4"
          style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 1.75rem); font-weight: 700; color: hsl(107 76% 26%); line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
        >
          Xbox Gamertag Generator Options Explained
        </h2>

        <p class="mb-6" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
          This generator has four filter options. Each one changes the type of names you get. Here is what each option does and when to use it.
        </p>

        <!-- Gender -->
        <h3 class="mb-2" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.15rem); font-weight: 700; color: #111827; line-height: 1.3;">
          Gender
        </h3>
        <p class="mb-5" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
          Choose <strong style="color: #111827;">male, female, or neutral</strong> to shape the style of your gamertag results. The female option works well for cute, aesthetic, or soft name styles. The male option leans toward cool, dark, sweaty, or competitive names. Neutral works for any player who wants clean, balanced name ideas that fit any gaming identity.
        </p>

        <!-- Character Theme -->
        <h3 class="mb-2" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.15rem); font-weight: 700; color: #111827; line-height: 1.3;">
          Character Theme
        </h3>
        <p class="mb-3" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
          Select a theme to define the feel of your gamertag ideas. Here are all available themes:
        </p>

        <div class="mb-6 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg" style="border: 1px solid #E5E7EB;">
          <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(14px, 1.8vw, 15px);">
            <thead>
              <tr style="background-color: hsl(107 76% 26%); color: #ffffff;">
                <th style="padding: 10px 16px; text-align: left; font-weight: 600; white-space: nowrap;">Theme</th>
                <th style="padding: 10px 16px; text-align: left; font-weight: 600;">Name Style</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr style="background-color: #ffffff;">
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #111827; font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB; white-space: nowrap;">Animals</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #374151; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB;">Names inspired by creatures, nature, and wildlife</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="background-color: #F4FAF0;">
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #111827; font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB; white-space: nowrap;">Fantasy</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #374151; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB;">Magical, mythical, and epic gamertag ideas</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="background-color: #ffffff;">
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #111827; font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB; white-space: nowrap;">Food</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #374151; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB;">Playful and funny food-based names</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="background-color: #F4FAF0;">
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #111827; font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB; white-space: nowrap;">Funny</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #374151; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB;">Humorous and lighthearted gamertag styles</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="background-color: #ffffff;">
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #111827; font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB; white-space: nowrap;">Gaming</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #374151; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB;">Names built around gaming culture and references</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="background-color: #F4FAF0;">
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #111827; font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB; white-space: nowrap;">Music</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #374151; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB;">Names inspired by music, sound, and rhythm</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="background-color: #ffffff;">
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #111827; font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB; white-space: nowrap;">Space</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #374151; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB;">Cosmic, sci-fi, and galaxy-themed names</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="background-color: #F4FAF0;">
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #111827; font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB; white-space: nowrap;">Sports</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #374151; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB;">Athletic and competitive name ideas</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="background-color: #ffffff;">
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #111827; font-weight: 600; white-space: nowrap;">Tech</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px 16px; color: #374151;">Digital, cyber, and technology-themed names</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <!-- Language -->
        <h3 class="mb-2" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.15rem); font-weight: 700; color: #111827; line-height: 1.3;">
          Language
        </h3>
        <p class="mb-5" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
          The generator supports <strong style="color: #111827;">14 languages</strong> — Arabic, English, French, German, Hindi, Indonesian, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Polish, Portuguese, Russian, Spanish, and Turkish. Select your preferred language before generating to get name ideas that match that language style.
        </p>

        <!-- Name Preference -->
        <h3 class="mb-2" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.15rem); font-weight: 700; color: #111827; line-height: 1.3;">
          Name Preference
        </h3>
        <p class="mb-0" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
          The name preference filter controls the format of your results. <strong style="color: #111827;">Default</strong> gives you standard suggestions with no restrictions. <strong style="color: #111827;">Short name</strong> generates shorter ideas that are easier to read on friend lists and leaderboards. <strong style="color: #111827;">No numbers</strong> avoids names with number suffixes so your gamertag looks cleaner on your Xbox profile. <strong style="color: #111827;">Short with no numbers</strong> combines both — short names and no numbers — for the cleanest possible output.
        </p>
      </div>




 <section
  class="pt-8 md:pt-16 pb-8"
  style="background-color: #ffffff; width: 100vw; position: relative; left: 50%; right: 50%; margin-left: -50vw; margin-right: -50vw;"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 md:px-12">
      <!-- ─── H2-3: Generate by Character Length ─── -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2
          class="mt-6 mb-4"
          style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 1.75rem); font-weight: 700; color: hsl(107 76% 26%); line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
        >
          Generate Xbox Gamertags by Character Length
        </h2>

        <p class="mb-4" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
          Xbox gamertags can be up to 12 characters long. Shorter names look cleaner on leaderboards, friend lists, and Xbox profiles. Many players look specifically for 3-letter, 4-letter, or 5-letter gamertag ideas because short names are harder to get and easier to remember.
        </p>

        <ul class="mb-5 space-y-2" style="list-style: disc; padding-left: 1.5rem;">
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            <strong style="color: #111827;">3 letters</strong> — ultra rare and clean, the hardest to get
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            <strong style="color: #111827;">4 letters</strong> — short, sharp, and easy to remember
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            <strong style="color: #111827;">5 letters</strong> — more options while still short and readable
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            <strong style="color: #111827;">6 to 8 letters</strong> — most common range, good balance of creativity and readability
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            <strong style="color: #111827;">9 to 12 letters</strong> — more creative freedom, full character limit
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mb-0" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
          Use the <strong style="color: #111827;">short name</strong> or <strong style="color: #111827;">short with no numbers</strong> preference to focus on shorter results. Then use our
          <a href="/xbox-gamertag-availability-checker" style="color: hsl(107 76% 26%); text-decoration: underline; font-weight: 600;">Xbox Gamertag Availability Checker</a>
          to see if your preferred name is still available on Xbox Live.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- ─── H2-4: Xbox Gamertag Rules ─── -->
      <div class="mb-0">
        <h2
          class="mt-6 mb-4"
          style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 1.75rem); font-weight: 700; color: hsl(107 76% 26%); line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
        >
          Xbox Gamertag Rules to Know
        </h2>

        <p class="mb-4" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
          Before choosing a final name, here are the key Xbox gamertag rules to keep in mind.
        </p>

        <ul class="mb-5 space-y-2" style="list-style: disc; padding-left: 1.5rem;">
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            Gamertags can be up to <strong style="color: #111827;">12 characters</strong> including spaces
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            Offensive names, impersonation, and banned words are <strong style="color: #111827;">not allowed</strong>
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            Symbols and special characters have restrictions
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            If a name is taken, Xbox may add a <strong style="color: #111827;">number suffix</strong> automatically to keep your gamertag unique
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.75; color: #374151;">
            Your <strong style="color: #111827;">first gamertag change is free</strong> — additional changes may cost a fee depending on your region
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mb-0" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 16px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
          For the full breakdown of what is and is not allowed, read our
          <a href="/xbox-gamertag-rules" style="color: hsl(107 76% 26%); text-decoration: underline; font-weight: 600;">Xbox Gamertag Rules</a> guide.
        </p>
      </div>
</div></section>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>